==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Possible
<hw>Pos"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>possibilis</ets>, fr. <ets>posse</ets> to be able, to have power;
<ets>potis</ets> able, capable + <ets>esse</ets> to be. See
<er>Potent</er>, <er>Am</er>, and cf. <er>Host</er> a landlord.]</ety>
<def>Capable of existing or occurring, or of being conceived or thought
of; able to happen; capable of being done; not contrary to the nature of
things; -- sometimes used to express extreme improbability; barely able
to be, or to come to pass; <as>as, possibly he is honest, as it is
<ex>possible</ex> that Judas meant no wrong</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With God all things are <qex>possible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Matt.
xix. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Practicable; likely. See
<er>Practicable</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Possibly</ent>⟦br⟧
